Refactor: Unify all 8 operator types to use protocol-based factory pattern

Complete the operator architecture standardization by extending the
protocol-based factory pattern to all remaining operator categories
(boundary, force, initialise, differential), building on the foundation
established for collision, streaming, equilibrium, and macroscopic
operators.

ARCHITECTURAL IMPROVEMENTS
- All 8 operator types now follow identical discovery and instantiation
  pattern: Protocol interface → Registry → Factory function → Type-safe
  wrapper in __init__.py
- Eliminated boilerplate in boundary, force, initialise, and differential
  operator packages
- Established clear public/private boundaries: implementation files renamed
  to private modules (_bgk.py, _gradient.py, etc.)

CHANGES BY OPERATOR CATEGORY

Boundary Operators:
- Refactored src/operators/boundary/__init__.py to use build_boundary_fn()
- Renamed: bounce_back.py → _bounce_back.py, periodic.py → _periodic.py,
  symmetry.py → _symmetry.py
- Uses lazy imports to avoid circular dependency with composite.py

Force Operators:
- Refactored src/operators/force/__init__.py to use build_force_fn()
- Keeps public module names (electric.py, gravity.py) - not renamed
- Uses lazy imports in factory

Initialisation Operators:
- Refactored src/operators/initialise/__init__.py to use
  build_initialise_fn()
- No files renamed (11 implementation modules remain public)
- Maintains backward-compatible legacy get_init_fn() in factory.py
- Fixed all 11 initialise modules to import from ._equilibrium instead of
  .equilibrium

Differential Operators:
- Refactored src/operators/differential/__init__.py to use
  build_differential_fn()
- Renamed: gradient.py → _gradient.py, laplacian.py → _laplacian.py
- Uses lazy imports to avoid circular dependency with simulation_setup.py

IMPORT FIXES
Updated ~40 import statements across source and test files:
- src/setup/simulation_setup.py: boundary imports from private modules
- src/runner/step.py: streaming_fn() instead of undefined stream()
- src/runner/run.py: build_initialise_fn() instead of get_init_fn()
- src/operators/boundary/composite.py: private module imports
- tests/test_pure_operators.py: updated collision, streaming, macroscopic
- tests/test_differential.py: gradient, laplacian imports
- tests/test_force_operators.py: streaming imports
- tests/test_initialise.py: factory imports, backward-compat usage

CIRCULAR IMPORT RESOLUTION
Used lazy evaluation (imports inside factory functions) to resolve
circular dependencies:
- boundary/__init__.py ↔ boundary/composite.py
- differential/__init__.py ↔ simulation_setup.py
- force/__init__.py ↔ step.py

TEST RESULTS
- 390 tests PASSED (all refactoring-related functionality)
- 2 tests SKIPPED (optional dependencies)
- 8 tests FAILED (pre-existing failures unrelated to this refactoring)

The 8 failing tests are in the wetting module (TestUpdateWettingState,
TestStepMultiphaseWithWetting) and stem from a pre-existing logic error in
src/operators/wetting/hysteresis.py where the code assumes
compute_macroscopic("standard") always returns 3 values, but it returns
only 2 when no force is provided. This bug was not introduced by this
refactoring (wetting module was not modified) and should be addressed in
a separate PR.

BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
- All public APIs preserved
- Optional dependencies installed: optax, click, rich, tomli_w
- Legacy get_init_fn() maintained in operators/initialise/factory.py
- All tests passing except pre-existing wetting failures

Files modified: ~42 files (renames, imports, factory refactoring)
Lines affected: ~300 (factory implementations, import updates)
